  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Expositor's Greek Testament",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "John 8:39",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". To this ambiguous but ominous utterance the Jews reply: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "Ὁ πατὴρ ἡμῶν Ἀβραάμ ἐστι",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", thereby meaning to clear themselves of the suspicion of having learned anything evil from their father. To which Jesus retorts: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "Εἰ τέκνα",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " … ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "ἐποιεῖτε ἄν",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". “If ye were Abraham’s children ye would do the works of Abraham”; according to the law of ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "John 8:38",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". If their origin could be wholly traced to Abraham, then their conduct would resemble his.—",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "νῦν δὲ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " … ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "ἐποίησεν",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". “But now—as the fact really is—you seek to kill me; and this has not only the guilt of an ordinary murder, but your hostility is roused against me because I have spoken to you the truth I heard from God. It is murder based upon hostility to God. This is very different from the conduct of Abraham.”—",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "ἄνθρωπον",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " seems to be used simply as we might use “person”—a person who: certainly, as Lampe says, it is used “sine praejudicio deitatis”. Bengel thinks it anticipates ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "ἀνθρωπόκτονος",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " in ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "John 8:44",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", and Westcott says it “stands in contrast with ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "of God",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " … and at the same time suggests the idea of human sympathy, which He might claim from them (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "a man",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "), as opposed to the murderous spirit of the power of evil”.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
        "text": "",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "br",
            "class": "",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
